The paper deals with subgame perfect equilibria in games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the characterization of families of linear preferences, which can be seen as a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also presents results for non-linear preferences, which can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
